{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771236218,"nonce":"SHKhzAANuR8mIoahhHqxJULl9bE=","title":"Disable or protect Devise user registration route","message":"The /register/register route (Devise registerable) is publicly accessible but unusable: submitting it fails because User requires department_memberships, firstname, and lastname which the form doesn't have.\n\nUsers are created via devise_invitable (admin/leader sends invitation). The Devise registration route serves no purpose and confuses the UX.\n\nOptions:\n1. Remove :registerable from User model entirely (users can only be invited)\n2. If :registerable is needed for Devise internals (profile edit), use skip: [:new, :create] in routes\n\nNote: /registrieren is the borrower self-registration route (different thing entirely).","files":null}]}